This paper is about open-domain human-computer conversation, which falls under the category of natural language processing (NLP). The paper proposes a novel ensemble of retrieval-based and generation-based dialog systems, which involves the use of recurrent neural networks (RNNs). Therefore, the most likely sub-category is cs.CL (Computation and Language), which deals with NLP and machine learning. Other likely sub-categories include cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence), cs.LG (Machine Learning), cs.IR (Information Retrieval), and cs.SD (Software Engineering).
